Scientific:   Stomatopoda
Class:        Malacostraca
Habitat:      Tropical ocean
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     20 years
Weight:       0.1 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Fastest punch in animal kingdom; 16 types of color receptors

Name:         Octopus
Scientific:   Octopus vulgaris
Class:        Cephalopoda
Habitat:      Ocean
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     3 years
Weight:       10 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         3 hearts, blue blood; changes color in 0.3 seconds; 9 brains

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Malaria
Type:        Parasitic
Pathogen:    Plasmodium falciparum
Transmission:Mosquito bite
Symptoms:    Fever, chills, sweating cycles
Treatment:   Artemisinin combination therapy
Deaths/yr:   0.619M
Vaccine:     Yes (RTS,S approved 2021)
Discovered:  1880

Disease:     COVID-19
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    SARS-CoV-2
Transmission:Respiratory droplets
Symptoms:    Fever, cough, loss of smell
Treatment:   Antivirals, supportive care
Deaths/yr:   5.0M
Vaccine:     Yes (mRNA vaccines)
Discovered:  2019

Disease:     Hepatitis B
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HBV
Transmission:Blood, sexual contact
Symptoms:    Often asymptomatic; jaundice
Treatment:   Antivirals (tenofovir)
Deaths/yr:   0.82M
Vaccine:     Yes (highly effective)
Discovered:  1965

